cs.NE, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.MA, cs.SY. 

The paper is about a mini-application benchmark for plastic spiking neural network simulators, which is a topic related to neural networks and distributed computing. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the strong and weak scaling of the benchmark on a commodity cluster, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The mini-application is designed to be easily interfaced with standard and custom software and hardware communication interfaces, which is related to cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). Finally, the paper discusses the profiling of computational and communication components, which is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
